# Terminal Quote Generator

Global PowerShell-friendly quote generator with live quotes, local caching, and styled terminal output.

## Install

```powershell
cd C:\terminal-quotes
py -3 -m pip install -e .
```

After that, you can run:

```powershell
quote-gen
```

from any PowerShell directory.

## File structure

```text
C:\terminal-quotes
├─ pyproject.toml
├─ setup.py
├─ README.md
└─ src
   └─ terminal_quote_generator
      ├─ __init__.py
      └─ cli.py
```

## What it does

- Fetches random quotes from `https://zenquotes.io`
- Uses your terminal width to wrap text cleanly
- Saves config and cache under `%APPDATA%\TerminalQuoteGenerator\`
- Falls back to cached output when offline or within the configured refresh interval

## Configuration

On first run, the app creates:

`%APPDATA%\TerminalQuoteGenerator\config.ini`

Default settings:

- `interval_minutes = 60`
- `theme_color = MAGENTA`

It also stores cache at:

`%APPDATA%\TerminalQuoteGenerator\cache.json`
